        </ul>

        <section id="add-claim">
            <h3>Add Claims</h3>
            <p>To add a new claim, follow these steps:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Navigate to the <a href="/claims/search">Claims Search</a> page.</li>
                <li>Click on the "Add Claim" button.</li>
                <li>Fill in the required fields including MVA, Customer Name, Description, and Status.</li>
                <li>Upload any necessary files.</li>
                <li>Click the "Submit" button to save the claim.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>

        <section id="edit-claim">
            <h3>Edit Claims</h3>
            <p>To edit an existing claim, follow these steps:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Navigate to the <a href="/claims/search">Claims Search</a> page.</li>
                <li>Search for the claim you want to edit.</li>
                <li>Click on the claim to open the detail view.</li>
                <li>Update the necessary fields.</li>
                <li>Click the "Save Changes" button to update the claim.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>

        <section id="search-claims">
            <h3>Search Claims</h3>
            <p>To search for claims, follow these steps:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Navigate to the <a href="/claims/search">Claims Search</a> page.</li>
                <li>Enter the search criteria such as MVA or Customer Name.</li>
                <li>Click the "Search" button to find matching claims.</li>
                <li>Click on a claim in the search results to view or edit it.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>

        <section id="export-claims">
            <h3>Export Claims</h3>
            <p>To export claims to a file, follow these steps:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Navigate to the <a href="/claims/search">Claims Search</a> page.</li>
                <li>Search for the claims you want to export.</li>
                <li>Click the "Export" button and select the desired format (CSV, Excel, or PDF).</li>
                <li>The file will be downloaded to your computer.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>

        <section id="generate-reports">
            <h3>Generate Reports</h3>
            <p>To generate reports, follow these steps:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Navigate to the <a href="/reports">Reports</a> page.</li>
                <li>Select the report type (PDF, CSV, or Excel) from the dropdown menu.</li>
                <li>Click the "Generate Report" button.</li>
                <li>The report will be generated and downloaded to your computer.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>

        <section id="user-management">
            <h3>User Management</h3>
            <p>To manage users, follow these steps:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Navigate to the <a href="/users">User Management</a> page.</li>
                <li>To create a new user, fill in the required fields (Name, Email, Password) and click the "Create User" button.</li>
                <li>To delete a user, enter the User ID and click the "Delete User" button.</li>
                <li>To modify user permissions, enter the User ID and new permissions, then click the "Modify Permissions" button.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>

        <h3>Support</h3>
        <p>If you need further assistance, please contact our support team at <a href="mailto:support@budgetclaims.com">support@budgetclaims.com</a>.</p>
